This is my go-to lamb recipe if we're having a dinner party. It's easy to prepare the night before, and then put it on the BBQ. The recipe as posted originally on epicurious called for "olive oil paste". You will see references to that in early reviews. It was a misprint, apparently, but I have to say having made it both ways (with olive paste--like a black olive tapenade) and with just olive oil--it's better with the crushed black olives mixed into the herb mixture. Read the earlier reviews and you'll see what I mean. It's a really good, very easy recipe.

