Rating: 4
This is the best lamb recipe I've ever made. To cook it, though I followed advice of Cook's Illustrated. I didn't skewer the meat as noted above, but created a quite hot fire on one side of the grill and left the other cooler. Then I seared the fat side for a few minutes, then turned over to sear the other side. I then moved over to the 'cold' side of the grill, instead of leaving over fire and closed the lid. Cooked for 10 minutes per pound on each side. Came out perfect! I served with lemony-argula and mashed potatoes, and made a reduction sauce with beef stock and the lamb bone. Like others, I pureed Olives with some olive oil to make the paste. (The olives and coarse salt are key to this recipe, as is rubbing the lamb with the lemon.) Great! Will definitely make again.

