Rating: 3
The real beauty of this recipe is the cooking instructions. I combined all of the ingredients with a cup of olive oil and marinated the lamb overnight in the fridge. Brought it back to room temp before putting it on the grill. This was a very large butterfly (7 lbs.) so I cut it in half at the seam. One slab was thicker than the other. I put them both on at the same time and cooked for exactly the amount of time specified in the recipe. After letting it sit for 15 minutes, I sliced the thicker side (about 3inches ) for perfectly done med. rare meat and sliced the thinner side (about an inch and a half) for medium slices. So, everyone got to have their lamb to their desired doneness. This was the easiest Easter dinner I've prepared in years. And delicious too!

